## Add the crate to your application

This folder is a self-contained Cargo crate. From your consuming crate's `Cargo.toml`:

```toml
[dependencies]
{{tii.protocol.name}} = { path = "path/to/this/folder" }
tx3-sdk = "0.12"
```

Cargo picks up the generated crate's own dependency on `tx3-sdk` automatically; the explicit entry above is only needed if your application code also imports `tx3_sdk` directly.

If you need a local dev runtime, `trix devnet` exposes a TRP endpoint at `http://localhost:8164`.

## Use the client

```rust
use tx3_sdk::{Party, trp::ClientOptions};
use {{tii.protocol.name}}::{Client, Profile};

let client = Client::new(
    ClientOptions { endpoint: "http://localhost:8164".into(), headers: None },
    Profile::Local,
);
```

Each `tx` declared by the protocol becomes a typed method on `client`, returning the `resolve → sign → submit → wait` lifecycle. See the [Tx3 consuming guide](https://docs.txpipe.io/tx3/consuming/quick-start) for the full walkthrough.
